<p>In 2010, the maize planted area for all purposes in the US was estimated at 35 million hectares (87.9 million acres),<sup id="cite_ref-80" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-80">[79]</a></sup> following an increasing trend since 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-81" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-81">[80]</a></sup> About 14% of the harvested corn area is irrigated.<sup id="cite_ref-82" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-82">[81]</a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Pests">Pests</span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Insects">Insects</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/African_armyworm" title="African armyworm">African armyworm</a> (<i>Spodoptera exempta</i>)</li>
<li>Common armyworm (<i><a href="/wiki/Pseudaletia_unipuncta" class="mw-redirect" title="Pseudaletia unipuncta">Pseudaletia unipuncta</a></i>)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Common_earwig" class="mw-redirect" title="Common earwig">Common earwig</a> (<i>Forficula auricularia</i>)</li>
