<li><a href="/wiki/Stalk_Borer" class="mw-redirect" title="Stalk Borer">Stalk borer</a> (<i>Papaipema nebris</i>)</li>
</ul>
<p>The susceptibility of maize to the European corn borer and corn rootworms, and the resulting large crop losses which are estimated at a billion dollars worldwide for each pest,<sup id="cite_ref-83" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-83">[82]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-84" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-84">[83]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-85" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-85">[84]</a></sup> led to the development of <a href="/wiki/Transgenic_plants" class="mw-redirect" title="Transgenic plants">transgenics</a> expressing the <i><a href="/wiki/Bacillus_thuringiensis" title="Bacillus thuringiensis">Bacillus thuringiensis</a></i> toxin. "Bt maize" is widely grown in the United States and has been approved for release in Europe.</p>
